#N canvas 0 23 455 580 10;
#X obj 21 18 uoscil/wander~;
#X text 114 18 RANDOM WANDERING VALUE WITH GRAVITATIONAL PULL;
#X text 18 48 Generates a wandering value between -1 and 1 \, tending
towards 0 A weighted random chance is used to keep the value centred
around 0 \; at 1 there is a 100% chance to go down \, at -1 100% chance
to go up \; and at 0 there is a 50/50 chance to go either up or down.
;
#X text 18 188 Velocity (maximum change per step) can also be set on
creation and via the right inlet.;
#X text 27 256 exponent of 1 (linear) and velocity of 0.05;
#X text 27 396 exponent of 4 and velocity of 0.05;
#X text 18 128 There is an adjustable exponential scaling factor to
the weighted chance (set on creation) \, i.e. the weights increase
exponentially instead of linearly as the value approaches the extremes.
Lower exponents will make the value stick more to 0 and higher exponents
the opposite.;
#X text 18 218 Takes up to two creation arguments (exponent \, velocity)
;
#X obj 53 324 uoscil/wander 1 0.05;
#X obj 53 464 uoscil/wander 4 0.05;
#X obj 53 283 tgl 15 0 empty empty empty 17 7 0 10 -262144 -1 -1 0
1;
